The Nigerian Ports Authority as majority shareholders along side other shareholders of the Agura Hotels, Abuja, have agreed to donate the 130-bedfully furnished hotel as isolation centre for COVID-19 in Abuja.  According to the statement endorsed by Jatto A Adams, General Manager, Corporate and Strategic Communications of the Authority disclosed that this is a social responsibility initiative aimed at supporting efforts of the Federal Government to contain the spread of the virus in Nigeria.  He added that the Authority encourages all Nigerians to follow all advisories issued by the National Centre for Disease Control and be confident that Nigeria shall overcome.